<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-64-0062 </DOCNO><TEXT>The author discusses the development of the European Community (EC), agroup of European nations who have grouped together to deal with Europeanproblems and the East-West issue. However, the author points out, theEC has not always been able to reach an agreement as to what it willsupport. The nations that make up the EC often do their own thing. Consequently,the EC is not recognized as a powerful force in world relations. Theauthor says the aim of the EC is to be a political body. However, atpresent it is an association of sovereign nations which changes withevery crisis and round of negotiations. Until Europe takes a major stepforward which will transform it into a real power, this will remain therole of the EC.</TEXT></DOC>